Summary of what's added:

1. Automatic save – Every time you add or delete a row, data is saved to localStorage
2. Automatic load – When you refresh the page, all your records reappear
3. Storage info button – Shows how much space your records are using
4. Clear all records button – Allows resetting to default example data (with confirmation prompt)
5. Cross-session persistence – Close the browser, come back days later, your data is still there

The localStorage limit is typically 5-10MB per domain, which is plenty for thousands of records. Your data stays on your own device/browser—perfect for personal tracking without needing a server.

